ity conversions according to § 8 (7) (Bundled booking points / conversion of firm unbundled capacity) and according to § 10 (Conversion of interruptible capacity or firm capacities with interruptible elements) of the terms and conditions for the entry and exit contract (entry-exit system) are implemented up to the amount of the smallest value from the new contract, old contract and conversion request (lesser-off rule).<br><br>The following link leads to the information whether or not over-nomination is currently possible at a specific networkpoint:\\n<a href=\\"https://tron-oge.publication.virtimo.cloud\\">UMM-Tool</a><br><br>", "gasType": "HGAS", "direction": "EXIT", "validFrom": "2022-04-02T06:00:00+02:00", "categories": ["8ed4e802-9e81-11ea-bb37-0242ac130002", "8ed4fb6c-9e81-11ea-bb37-0242ac130002", "8ed4ef1e-9e81-11ea-bb37-0242ac130002", "8ed4f2b6-9e81-11ea-bb37-0242ac130002", "8ed4e2e4-9e81-11ea-bb37-0242ac130002"], "congestion": false, "flowUnitId": "5bd05688-9f23-11ea-bb37-0242ac130002", "adjacentTso": "Fluxys SA", "marketAreaId": "63662dc6-9228-11eb-aa29-06c640c5cd26", "floatingCharge": true, "sellingMethods": ["UNKNOWN"], "tradingMarkets": ["PRIMARY", "SECONDARY"], "specificSecondary": false, "networkPointTypeId": "52c09888-9f3b-11ea-bb37-0242ac130002", "specificConditions": [], "undiscountedCharge": false, "ownerOrganisationId": "6e7d8a40-96ea-4fef-a026-fc788b1e7874", "publicAssignedNetworkPointId": "VIP-THE-ZTP-A", "internalAssignedNetworkPointId": "DVGW!?!9870047600001|VIP-THE-ZTP-A|EXIT"}, {"eic": "21Z102938475601E", "name": "VIP THE-ZTP", "active": true, "comment": "In the yearly auction at this Virtual Interconnection Point the involved German TSOs will market firm capacities for a different number of gas years:<br>\\n- FluxysTENP will market capacities for 15 gas years.<br>\\n- GASCADE, Open Grid Europe and Thyssengas will market capacities for five gas years.<br><br>\\n\\nOpen Grid Europe would like to inform the network users about potential capacity re-allocation at interconnection points (IPs). In order to meet changing capacity demand the German TSOs are obliged to re-allocate capacity between IPs and national connection points. This will ensure an efficient use of the existing capacity in Germany. If at the end of the auction for yearly or quarterly products, there are any unsold capacities, TSOs may re-allocate the capacity to alternative German connection points. However, this procedure can even work vice versa. If TSOs will observe an auction premium for yearly or quarterly capacity products, unsold capacity shall be re-allocated from one connection point to another to the extent legally or technically possible. <br><br>Capacity conversions according to § 8 (7) (Bundled booking points / conversion of firm unbundled capacity) and according to § 10 (Conversion of interruptible capacity or firm capacities with interruptible elements) of the terms and conditions for the entry and exit contract (entry-exit system) are implemented up to the amount of the smallest value from the new contract, old contract and conversion request (lesser-off rule).<br><br>The following link leads to the information whether or not over-nomination is currently possible at a specific networkpoint:\\n<a href=\\"https://tron-oge.publication.virtimo.cloud\\">UMM-Tool</a><br><br>", "gasType": "HGAS", "direction": "EXIT", "validFrom": "2022-05-20T06:00:00+02:00", "categories": ["8ed4e802-9e81-11ea-bb37-0242ac130002", "8ed4fb6c-9e81-11ea-bb37-0242ac130002", "8ed4ef1e-9e81-11ea-bb37-0242ac130002", "8ed4f2b6-9e81-11ea-bb37-0242ac130002", "8ed4e2e4-9e81-11ea-bb37-0242ac130002"], "congestion": false, "flowUnitId": "5bd05688-9f23-11ea-bb37-0242ac130002", "adjacentTso": "Fluxys SA", "marketAreaId": "63662dc6-9228-11eb-aa29-06c640c5cd26", "floatingCharge": true, "sellingMethods": ["UNKNOWN"], "tradingMarkets": ["PRIMARY", "SECONDARY"], "specificSecondary": false, "networkPointTypeId": "52c09888-9f3b-11ea-bb37-0242ac130002", "specificConditions